sentences: Jonathan Zazula (March 16, 1952 – February 1, 2022), also known as Jonny Z, was an American music industry executive who was the owner of New Jersey's Rock'n Roll Heaven record store and founder of record label Megaforce Records.
In 2019, Zazula released an auto-biography titled Heavy Tales.
Zazula was born on March 16, 1952, and was Jewish.
His second wife, Marsha Zazula (née Marsha Jean Rutenberg; 1952–2021), was his partner and co-founder at Megaforce Records.
They were married from 1979 until Marsha's death on January 10, 2021.
They were married from 1979 until Marsha's death on January 10, 2021.
He died at his home in Clermont on February 1, 2022, at the age of 69, from complications of chronic inflammatory demyelinating polyneuropathy, COPD, and osteopenia.
His death occurred nearly thirteen months after Marsha's death.
